This paper deals with covert communication in a network environment, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of FTE and UDP-based protocols suggests a focus on network protocols and communication (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of Hidden Markov Models, which are commonly used in data analysis and machine learning (cs.DC). The implementation of the Protocol Proxy involves software engineering and system design (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the use of protected static protocols to avoid detection, which involves analyzing and manipulating network traffic (cs.DS).
